This project uses MJML (Mailjet Markup Language) to build responsive HTML emails.

## Key rules

- Always use https://documentation.mjml.io/#mjml-guide for guidelines on how to do stuff. Always inform if documentation was used and what parts were read.
- All layouts should prioritise using MJML components over raw HTML. If something can't be done with MJML components or would be messy/hard to work with - use <mj-raw>, which accepts plain HTML but cannot contain other MJML components.
- Required nesting: `<mjml>` → `<mj-body>` → `<mj-section>` → `<mj-column>` → content.
- Compiled HTML output goes to dist/ (not committed).

## Source layout

- `src/_styles/` — CSS files for inclusion via `<mj-include type="css">`
- `src/blocks/` — Reusable MJML fragments (partial markup); included with `<mj-include>`
- `src/components/` — Full MJML documents; compiled to both dist/components/ (snippets) and dist/components-raw/ (full HTML)
- `src/templates/` — Standalone email templates; compiled to dist/templates/

## Component outputs

Components compile to two targets:

- `dist/components/` — Post-processed snippets (body content + custom styles only); include in templates with `<mj-include path="../../dist/components/foo.html" type="html" />`
- `dist/components-raw/` — Full unmodified HTML; used for standalone use in emails or for debugging.

## Build commands

- `bun run build` — Compile everything (components, components-raw, templates)
- `bun run build-templates` — Compile templates only
- `bun run build-components` — Compile components → dist/components/ (snippets)
- `bun run build-components-raw` — Compile components → dist/components-raw/ (full HTML)
- `bun run build-watch` — Watch all three in parallel
- `bun run build-templates-watch` — Watch templates only
- `bun run build-components-watch` — Watch components (snippet output) only
- `bun run build-components-raw-watch` — Watch components (raw output) only
- `bun run build-minify` — Compile everything with minified output
- `bun run build-templates-minify` — Compile templates with minified output
- `bun run build-components-minify` — Compile components (snippets) with minified output
- `bun run build-components-raw-minify` — Compile components (raw) with minified output
